    <h1 id="who" class="bold offset">Who Benefits From HackMizzou?</h1>
    <div class="sep">STUDENTS</div>
    <p class="friendly">
      HackMizzou is centered around the 300 creative participants. HackMizzou provides the atmosphere conducive to technological advance and innovation due to its 36 hours of free food, potential prizes, and gathering of many passionate hackers.
    </p>
    <p class="friendly">
      The groups participating benefit by learning new technologies, networking with fellow hackers, and networking/applying with companies of potential future employment (internships and full-time).
    </p>
    <div class="sep">SPONSORS</div>
    <p class="friendly">
      The sponsors benefit because they can sample Mizzou's technological skills. If sponsors are more aware of Mizzou's hacking and technology skills and emphasis then they dedicate more resources to recruiting from Mizzou. This helps companies find talent, current students can find amazing internships, and recent grads find immediate employment at top notch companies.
    </p>
    <div class="sep">COLUMBIA, MISSOURI</div>
    <p class="friendly">
      Columbia benefits because this event is highly publicized as a center for innovation at Mizzou. Last year's event was notably mentioned by 10 nationally accredited news sources.
    </p>
    <div class="sep">UNIVERSITY OF MISSOURI</div>
    <p class="friendly">
      Because HackMizzou transports participants regionally, Mizzou is more known as a technological hub and it allows the University to speak for itself. We bus in students from University of Illinois, Washington University in Saint Louis, Perdue University, Rolla. We also have participants from Washington State, New York, and internationally. This is amazing exposure for Mizzou.
    </p>
    <div class="sep">SCHOOL OF ENGINEERING</div>
    <p class="friendly">
      The Engineering school benefits because it is a concrete example of successful programs hosted by its students. This is good for outreach and Engineering recruiting. It boasts the success of its students.
    </p>
